access to  running water, roads or electricity.  The big question is... is this South Africa we want?  Gogo Beka (52) has been living in Exmoor farm in Newcastle, KwaZulu Natal for more than 20 years. She says she cannot move from the farm since her late mother told her not to leave her behind. She survives by selling broom sticks. Gogo Beka (52) has been living in Exmoor farm in Newcastle; KwaZulu Natal for more than 20 years.Makhasaneni village in Newcastle KwaZulu Natal. Photo by Picture Hello. A man getting sun rays outside his mud house at Exmoor farm in Newcastle.Some of the mud houses belonging to Jeremiah Khanyi (61) from Exmoor farm in Newcstle in KwqaZulu Natal who survives by cattle farming. Some of the mud houses belonging to Jeremiah Khanyi (61) from Exmoor farm in Newcstle KwaZulu Natal who survives by cattle farming. Gogo Mothoni is one of the oldest community members of Fanpan farm in Lephalale Limpopo. She has never lived in a proper house. Some of the shacks from 40 families who lives at Fanpan farm in Lephalale where community members have never owned proper houses.  1/26
